1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,290
First, let's talk about the easiest way to get data files on hand.

2
00:00:04,290 --> 00:00:08,040
This is the case where an individual or an organization gathers the data

3
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:11,835
for you and simply hands over data files to you, the data wrangler.

4
00:00:11,835 --> 00:00:13,860
They may do this by, for example,

5
00:00:13,860 --> 00:00:17,640
sending the files via email or posting it on a Cloud storage service,

6
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:20,430
like Google Drive or Dropbox for you to download.

7
00:00:20,430 --> 00:00:23,220
They may also host the data on a website or

8
00:00:23,220 --> 00:00:26,610
a portal available to specific users or the general public.

9
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:29,445
When opening data files that were provided to you,

10
00:00:29,445 --> 00:00:33,375
ensure that you know that the final is safe to open by checking this source

11
00:00:33,375 --> 00:00:37,975
whether or not the file size seems accurate and potentially using a virus scanner.

12
00:00:37,975 --> 00:00:41,795
Check the file extension as well and open it via the right application,

13
00:00:41,795 --> 00:00:44,945
whether that's your operating systems notepad application,

14
00:00:44,945 --> 00:00:48,990
Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, or another application.

